<entry id="caber" guid="3b7f99b0-5444-528d-b6ba-de3c1c318183"><lexical-unit><form lang="es"><text>caber</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="caber_0" guid="60dd4b77-8149-55b6-aeb6-aafbcca371d0"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to fit, enter (to be able to be contained (by something; regardless of whether space or volume remains))</text></gloss></sense><sense id="caber_1" guid="d0f92917-96bc-5a13-b7a4-126bee79ab5d"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to traverse, pass through or across (a way, path, door, hole, opening, mouth, orifice, etc.)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="caber_2" guid="caccda34-abd3-51d6-bd57-bca1957ad343"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to be held or contained (to be held inside (something) or passed through (regardless of whether space or volume remains))</text></gloss></sense><sense id="caber_3" guid="9ad3668c-da85-5c48-83df-2b2e41112914"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to have, hold, should be (in certain phrases)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="caber_4" guid="dfd7f652-6c4a-5e4a-bfbb-f55703a9097a"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to be acceptable, accepted, permitted, permissible, allowable, etc.</text></gloss></sense><sense id="caber_5" guid="7755b3d3-4953-59f2-a377-f0e22c5411f9"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to take</text></gloss></sense><sense id="caber_6" guid="526cb083-fe8d-59ed-a7ea-e860b16847c8"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to understand</text></gloss></sense><sense id="caber_7" guid="eb9d34d8-50d0-587f-bd35-46ebcd008512"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to be possible</text></gloss></sense></entry>
