<entry id="desviar" guid="2752d094-6459-5e04-814e-c5487d710a0b"><lexical-unit><form lang="es"><text>desviar</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="desviar_0" guid="5951d1b1-a3d5-5d6d-a16a-18fc35c4e6d2"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to divert, to distract, to shift, to sidetrack</text></gloss></sense><sense id="desviar_1" guid="2863afa2-d4bd-5553-8936-99312ea94455"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to deflect</text></gloss></sense><sense id="desviar_2" guid="22a06322-97a8-51f1-9825-53a8733a0d46"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to derail (e.g. a movement, a process)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="desviar_3" guid="6bc0b4e5-abd6-5236-8f23-270ec2a7f314"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to bypass, to reroute, to redirect</text></gloss></sense><sense id="desviar_4" guid="e11b33b3-dc0e-5392-a7da-ff3611f3fe3e"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to siphon, to siphon off (e.g. money, funds)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="desviar_5" guid="c17581ca-cec3-515f-a749-8b900cb561c5"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to forward (a phone call)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="desviar_6" guid="284dd475-7842-5cdd-afee-98c1f6aace2d"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to avert (e.g. one's eyes or gaze)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="desviar_7" guid="fc1ff43c-5dea-5633-a07b-b8fa86da9478"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to change (e.g. the subject, the course, the conversation)</text></gloss></sense></entry>
