<entry id="mesopotamia" guid="58971499-37f4-5f18-b1b7-7f6c11ee6625"><lexical-unit><form lang="es"><text>mesopotamia</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="mesopotamia_0" guid="14c6e38c-123b-5aec-9249-2fa72acc86b0"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Mesopotamia (a geographic region in southwest Asia, spanning from the rivers Euphrates and Tigris, located in modern Iraq, eastern Syria, and southeast Turkey; the site of one of the most ancient civilizations in the history of man)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="mesopotamia_1" guid="e25e123d-cb90-5909-85d7-865e0c13a5e4"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Mesopotamia (a former province of the Roman Empire, existing from 116 to 117 AD and again from 198 to 637 AD)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="mesopotamia_2" guid="3bb1df42-1628-50b7-8d25-0baa896a1eec"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Mesopotamia (a geographic region in northeast Argentina, between the Paraná and Uruguay rivers)</text></gloss></sense></entry>
