<entry id="poner" guid="76fff03d-d5a8-536c-b24f-579a2c16662c"><lexical-unit><form lang="es"><text>poner</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="poner_0" guid="6c071c11-b593-5c73-afa3-427fc82eaf22"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to put, to put up, to place, to lay</text></gloss></sense><sense id="poner_1" guid="b7b876ce-0b7c-564e-97fc-69863c429a0d"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to set, to set up (e.g. set an alarm, set up chairs)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="poner_2" guid="9a91387e-583e-5135-8b5a-e68088c2b62e"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to put on (e.g. put on a smile, a happy face, a brave face; put on a pot of coffee, put something on display)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="poner_3" guid="1f0e9477-6108-533f-86cf-3c57793d436b"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to choose, to designate (for a job, charge or responsibility)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="poner_4" guid="94223430-1cff-5554-bd6e-e04ae028f939"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to make (e.g. make somebody nervous, jealous, sad, emotional, uncomfortable)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="poner_5" guid="29cfc86c-92db-5331-a067-52f425b80929"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to make, to give (in certain phrases; e.g. to make available, give an injection, to give effect)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="poner_6" guid="caeebdce-cc2c-5e18-9122-4f10beff762d"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to say, to read (statement: indicate in written form)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="poner_7" guid="e44ca227-4b0e-5459-b57a-1e1964a4dfba"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to name, to give a nickname</text></gloss></sense></entry>
