<entry id="romano" guid="2abfc8c5-5457-5389-9a0a-9a5390acfd7a"><lexical-unit><form lang="es"><text>romano</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="romano_0" guid="a9bbf404-bab9-54d5-ae91-ae69e985d154"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Roman (of, from or relating to the city of Rome, capital of Italy)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="romano_1" guid="03f47d6a-8511-5c91-b713-a18c3eda592d"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Roman (of, from or relating to Rome (ancient empire covering much of the land surrounding the Mediterranean))</text></gloss></sense><sense id="romano_2" guid="7a1a7e03-deeb-5694-b102-280dd1fce9e2"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>of Rome as the seat of power of the popes, heads of the Roman Catholic Church</text></gloss></sense><sense id="romano_3" guid="cd52951e-ccf2-5b8b-9d9c-825c0ab29342"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Roman (native or inhabitant of the city of Rome, capital of Italy) (usually male)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="romano_4" guid="708eac78-a0ed-5f60-bffb-8366f6d0379e"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Roman (native or inhabitant of Rome (ancient empire covering much of the land surrounding the Mediterranean)) (usually male)</text></gloss></sense></entry>
