<entry id="san" guid="517acf80-bffb-5325-ad63-66ed88bdf69f"><lexical-unit><form lang="es"><text>san</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="san_0" guid="d54a4f16-62fc-584f-8785-8c96ee0406fb"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>financial, temporal-savings scheme; the participants periodically contribute a quota to a communal pot that is given to one member, based on his/her turn amongst all the others</text></gloss></sense><sense id="san_1" guid="3fdba733-b3a0-5ac7-bf84-0e217cc20a43"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>apocopic form of santo (“saint”)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="san_2" guid="30ea63cb-0eff-54f5-a549-be2eab6cf939"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>san; the Greek letter Ϻ, ϻ</text></gloss></sense><sense id="san_3" guid="c59e72e4-d2ec-5da8-9916-2bee38d71aeb"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Saint (title)</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="sanar" guid="ea64f54b-272f-5449-a634-bc11375dbb88"><lexical-unit><form lang="es"><text>sanar</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="sanar_0" guid="a923120f-ca59-541c-a8d8-2b417b66d7fd"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to cure; to heal</text></gloss></sense><sense id="sanar_1" guid="0c529512-561d-5791-a87d-1eda883dcfd4"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to recover (from an illness)</text></gloss></sense></entry>
