<entry id="servir" guid="413cc905-aec2-53f7-a9f7-bd33915a41a8"><lexical-unit><form lang="es"><text>servir</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="servir_0" guid="ee56e9e8-0ce5-5e13-9e24-83f0b217a3a3"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to serve (to be a servant or worker; to render service)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="servir_1" guid="f1ab00bc-f78d-5dd1-b32e-75a36519453d"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to serve (to be a servant for; to work for)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="servir_2" guid="98695f69-33a9-592a-a8a8-1968eed35a42"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to be of use, to be good for</text></gloss></sense><sense id="servir_3" guid="4874713e-4b1f-5ac5-b7a2-a27a75fe4d6a"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to serve (to usefully take the place of something else)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="servir_4" guid="e2782f55-28eb-54d2-a4dc-7f5a248cf201"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to serve (to be in military service)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="servir_5" guid="4675a993-9a15-5b26-857e-3e34bbc96c2b"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to serve (to set down (food or drink) on the table to be eaten)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="servir_6" guid="f482e6a3-167a-5aca-8e2e-3c67f8e7b1e5"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to serve (to lead off with the first delivery over the net in tennis, volleyball, ping pong, badminton, etc.)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="servir_7" guid="528930d0-81d0-57b1-aff1-5cd9337f4005"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to help oneself to (to take freely)</text></gloss></sense></entry>
