<entry id="sí" guid="bd9f49ed-91f2-5afd-b957-4c6fe798ffb5"><lexical-unit><form lang="es"><text>sí</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="sí_0" guid="1e102f19-097a-5aaf-bcea-9890ba13868e"><grammatical-info value="Interjection"/><gloss lang="en"><text>yes, yeah, (used to respond affirmatively to a question, used both informally and formally)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="sí_1" guid="c49c96af-e47c-5ecd-99df-2dc659c4f44f"><grammatical-info value="Interjection"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Used to give positive emphasis to a verb, which is often replaced. Functions similarly to English do.</text></gloss></sense><sense id="sí_2" guid="6225a7bf-9b2c-5adb-98a2-cda8ea8b6e89"><grammatical-info value="Interjection"/><gloss lang="en"><text>hello? (used when answering a phone call)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="sí_3" guid="6be4e6de-0cde-5e6e-8f60-0ef8d3f85d3a"><grammatical-info value="Interjection"/><gloss lang="en"><text>yes; aye, ay; approbation, acceptance</text></gloss></sense><sense id="sí_4" guid="d453eb24-35d7-518d-a467-128c4cf0f78e"><grammatical-info value="Interjection"/><gloss lang="en"><text>prepositional form of se</text></gloss></sense><sense id="sí_5" guid="5b07d985-79e3-5f13-93be-cdaf24ecb79f"><grammatical-info value="Interjection"/><gloss lang="en"><text>himself, herself, itself, themself, themselves</text></gloss></sense><sense id="sí_6" guid="b0707378-3eb8-5425-b1d5-70066ba2d3cb"><grammatical-info value="Interjection"/><gloss lang="en"><text>yourself, yourselves</text></gloss></sense></entry>
