<entry id="y" guid="355afe65-78ec-5ed1-88f7-bd5b1648ea08"><lexical-unit><form lang="es"><text>y</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="y_0" guid="c19ceeeb-d9ad-506a-b53f-8c0d2fcaaac2"><grammatical-info value="Coordinating connective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>The twenty-sixth letter of the Spanish alphabet, called ye or i griega and written in the Latin script.</text></gloss></sense><sense id="y_1" guid="88d85e91-6d6d-53ef-8787-aa4f5a83e7f1"><grammatical-info value="Coordinating connective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>and</text></gloss></sense><sense id="y_2" guid="56d628f2-2c7d-5cb4-b0bb-ebc6731da097"><grammatical-info value="Coordinating connective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>plus, and</text></gloss></sense><sense id="y_3" guid="20c158f0-0950-569d-808e-bb054f4d157d"><grammatical-info value="Coordinating connective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>well</text></gloss></sense><sense id="y_4" guid="3dae9caf-477b-5638-8d1c-d11cfd13c78b"><grammatical-info value="Coordinating connective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>what about, how about, and, where is/are the</text></gloss></sense><sense id="y_5" guid="c3f88ad3-34da-516f-97e2-11021e33bd10"><grammatical-info value="Coordinating connective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>The twenty-sixth letter of the Spanish alphabet, written in the Latin script.</text></gloss></sense></entry>
